Compose different


Recent research in AI-assisted music tools is opening new horizons for art creation. By learning on huge corpuses of existing sound pieces, a computer is able, on the one hand, to extract features from a sound and to learn notions such as structure, genre or even mood.  Such systems are already widespread for music analysis tasks such as tempo detection, lyrics and melody transcription and many other. 








On the other hand, such systems are also able to model music sequences and to generate new ones using the corpus to learn harmony, chord progressions or timbre. However, as opposed to the former application, using AI based assistants is still perceived as Composing music is a constantly evolving process. Indeed, from tribal percussions and rhythms to elkectronic dance music, composers have came a long way.